title: ICE: generic_const_exprs "range end index 2 out of range for slice of length 1"

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
### Code `rustc "-Zcrate-attr=feature(generic_const_exprs)"` ```Rust trait Trait { fn fnc(&self) -> Trait { bar } } fn main() {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.67.0-nightly (234151769 2022-12-03) binary: rustc commit-hash: 23415176968e81e0aac92d0218612a89c4e68a82 commit-date: 2022-12-03 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.67.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.4 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0403]: the name `N` is already used for a generic parameter in this item's generic parameters --> 152f764c6622dfef067008fe2bb5329872ae96ed.rs:2:18 | 1 | trait Trait { | - first use of `N` 2 | fn fnc(&self) -> Trait { | ^ already used error[E0425]: cannot find value `bar` in this scope --> 152f764c6622dfef067008fe2bb5329872ae96ed.rs:1:30 | 1 | trait Trait { | ^^^ not found in this scope error[E0423]: expected value, found builtin type `u32` --> 152f764c6622dfef067008fe2bb5329872ae96ed.rs:2:29 | 2 | fn fnc(&self) -> Trait { | ^^^ not a value error[E0425]: cannot find value `bar` in this scope --> 152f764c6622dfef067008fe2bb5329872ae96ed.rs:3:9 | 3 | bar | ^^^ not found in this scope warning: the feature `generic_const_exprs` is incomplete and may not be safe to use and/or cause compiler crashes --> :1:9 | 1 | feature(generic_const_exprs) | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = note: see issue #76560 for more information = note: `#[warn(incomplete_features)]` on by default warning: trait objects without an explicit `dyn` are deprecated --> 152f764c6622dfef067008fe2bb5329872ae96ed.rs:1:22 | 1 | trait Trait { | ^^^^^ | = warning: this is accepted in the current edition (Rust 2015) but is a hard error in Rust 2021!
